SIMPLE: typify
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Typify
<hw>Typ"i*fy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Typified</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Typifying</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[<ets>Type</ets> +
<ets>-fy</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To represent by an image, form,
model, or resemblance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our Savior was <qex>typified</qex>, indeed, by the goat that was
slain, and the scapegoat in the wilderness.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T.
Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To embody the essential or salient characteristics
of; to be the type of; <as>as, the genus <gen>Rosa</gen>
<ex>typifies</ex> the family <fam>Rosaceae</fam>, which in turn
<ex>typifies</ex> the series <ord>Rosales</ord></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Typist</ent>⟦br⟧
